article.headline: Radford 94, Shenandoah 63
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver scored 22 points and Kenny Thomas had 21 Saturday night to lead Radford to a 94-63 victory against Division III Shenandoah. Radford (5-6) used a 17-2 run to open a 24-8 lead with 8:13 left in the first half. The margin was 42-23 at halftime and Shenandoah got no closer than 17 in the second half. The Hornets (2-3) were led by Jeremiah Lawrence and Onyie Onunaku with 16 points each. Onunaku also grabbed 11 rebounds. Amir Johnson added 11 points, eight assists and five of Radford's 17 steals.
